Graham Flan | No Bake, No Oven, No Steam, No Mixer
Ingredients: 
For the custard cupcake:
1 cup crushed graham
1/4 cup melted butter
2 egg yolks
2 whole eggs
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup evaporated milk
1/3 cup condensed milk
2 pack unflavored gelatin (7g each)
Â½ cold water
For the caramel:
1/3 cup white sugar
2 tbsp water
1 tbsp corn starch
Â½ cup water
yield: 9pcs regular cupcake size
FULL RECIPE: https://youtu.be/V_JPn71gZgg
Procedure:
1.In a bowl, combine the crushed graham and melted butter. Mix well.
2.Line the muffin tray with the cupcake liners. Add  1.5-2 tbsp of graham in each liner. Press the crumbs mixture down and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
3.In a small bowl, mix the unflavored gelatin with cold water. Stir and let it bloom for 1-2 minutes. 
4.In a separate bowl. Add the whole eggs, egg yolks, evaporated milk, condensed milk and vanilla extract. Use a wire whisk to mix until well combined. Add the gelatin mixture and mix.
5.Put the stove over low-medium heat and transfer the mixture to the pan. Stir the mixture constantly and turn off the heat immediately when the mixture starts to boil.
6.Strain the mixture once. 
7.Pour the mixture in each liner. 
8.Poke to remove bubbles
9.Freeze for 15 minutes.
10.For the caramel, combine the water and corn starch in a small bowl and set it aside.
11.In a pan over medium-low heat. Add the sugar. Caramelized until amber in color. Then add 2 tbsp of water(optional) and let it boil once and add the corn starch water mixture. Stir constantly and cook for 3-5 minutes.
12.Pour on each graham cupcake. Refrigerate for at least 45 minutes. 
13.Serve and enjoy!
FULL RECIPE: https://youtu.be/V_JPn71gZgg
